8 An Act relating to wildlife; amending 29 O.S. 2021,
Section 7-304, as amended by Section 1, Chapter 19,
9 O.S.L. 2022 (29 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section 7-304),
which relates to wildlife refuges and Wildlife
10 Management Areas; requiring nonresident hunters to
receive permission from the Oklahoma Wildlife
11 Conservation Commission to use certain areas;
authorizing the Commission to create certain system
12 for permitting; requiring permit fee; providing for
promulgation of rules; updating statutory language;
13 and providing an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 29 O.S. 2021, Section 7-304, as
18 amended by Section 1, Chapter 19, O.S.L. 2022 (29 O.S. Supp. 2024,
19 Section 7-304), is amended to read as follows:
20 Section 7-304. A. Except as otherwise provided by law, no
21 person may enter upon any state or federal wildlife refuge or
22 Wildlife Management Area with a dog, a gun, or a bow.
